- 'Top 5' refers to the highest ranking based on the number of participants;
- 'Attracted the largest number of participants' means having the highest count of distinct participants.

sql:
SELECT experiment_id, SUM(totalTime) AS total_time 
FROM experiment_times 
GROUP BY experiment_id;

SELECT experiment_id, totalTime, experimentTime
FROM experiment_times
ORDER BY experiment_id ASC;

external_knowledge:
- "blossomed" refers to experiments that have successfully attracted a significant number of participants and high ratings;
- "rich tapestry of participation" refers to a high number of participants;
- "stellar ratings" refers to high average ratings;
- "multitude of trials" refers to a large number of trials;
- "garden of participants" refers to the number of participants;
- "harmonious blend" refers to the sum of the participant count, average rating, and trial count.

- "average accuracy" refers to the mean accuracy of the participant across all trials;
- "average reaction time" is the mean reaction time of the participant across all trials;
- "average rating" is the mean rating given by the participant across all ratings;
- "comprehensive dataset" includes the participant's ID, age, gender, average accuracy, and average rating.

- 'older than 20' refers to participants whose age is greater than 20;
- 'active' status indicates that the experiment is currently ongoing;
- '1-5' rating scale means the ratings are given on a scale from 1 to 5.

- 'Dr. John Doe' is the name of the principal investigator;
- 'Rating' is a measure of satisfaction or performance given by participants, with a higher number indicating a better rating;
- 'Reaction time' is the time it takes for a participant to respond to a stimulus in a trial.

- Performance metrics include average accuracy and average reaction time;
- Demographic details include age, gender, education level, and occupation;
- The query focuses on participants' performance in trials and their demographic characteristics.

- "Average trial duration" refers to the mean duration of trials within an experiment;
- "Semantic connotation" is a property of objects that can be linked to experiment versions;
- "More than 5 participants" means the experiment must have at least 6 participants;
- "Older than 20 years old" refers to participants aged 21 or above.
